description.displayText: Eleanor was a sitter for my elementary aged daughter back in San Francisco. She was always dependable and would come through for us in a clutch, which happened more than you'd expect in a city like SF. The trains would break down or I'd get held up at work sometimes. Eleanor was flexible and reliable. She had a great bond with my daughter who still asks about her to this day. We loved Eleanor, any family would be lucky to have her for a sitter.

description.displayText:
Eleanor is terrific! She babysat for us when our kids were young elementary age.

Our kids enjoyed having her as a babysitter, especially as she often thought ahead to plan some activities that they'd enjoy. She's by nature a very organized and responsible person, which felt very reassuring to us as parents.

We would definitely recommend her as a babysitter. She's a lovely person and very reliable.
